trans-unit.source: Provides <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.VisualStyles.VisualStyleElement"></xref> objects for each state of the upward-pointing arrow for a spin button control (also known as an up-down control).

Each property of the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.VisualStyles.VisualStyleElement.Spin.Up> class returns a <xref:System.Windows.Forms.VisualStyles.VisualStyleElement> for a different state of the upward-pointing arrow for a spin button.
Gets a visual style element that represents an upward-pointing spin button arrow in the disabled state.

You can use the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.VisualStyles.VisualStyleElement> returned by the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.VisualStyles.VisualStyleElement.Spin.Up.Disabled%2A> property to create a <xref:System.Windows.Forms.VisualStyles.VisualStyleRenderer>.
A <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.VisualStyles.VisualStyleElement"></xref> that represents an upward-pointing spin button arrow in the disabled state.
Gets a visual style element that represents an upward-pointing spin button arrow in the hot state.

You can use the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.VisualStyles.VisualStyleElement> returned by the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.VisualStyles.VisualStyleElement.Spin.Up.Hot%2A> property to create a <xref:System.Windows.Forms.VisualStyles.VisualStyleRenderer>.
A <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.VisualStyles.VisualStyleElement"></xref> that represents an upward-pointing spin button arrow in the hot state.
Gets a visual style element that represents an upward-pointing spin button arrow in the normal state.

You can use the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.VisualStyles.VisualStyleElement> returned by the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.VisualStyles.VisualStyleElement.Spin.Up.Normal%2A> property to create a <xref:System.Windows.Forms.VisualStyles.VisualStyleRenderer>.
A <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.VisualStyles.VisualStyleElement"></xref> that represents an upward-pointing spin button arrow in the normal state.
Gets a visual style element that represents an upward-pointing spin button arrow in the pressed state.

You can use the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.VisualStyles.VisualStyleElement> returned by the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.VisualStyles.VisualStyleElement.Spin.Up.Pressed%2A> property to create a <xref:System.Windows.Forms.VisualStyles.VisualStyleRenderer>.
A <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.VisualStyles.VisualStyleElement"></xref> that represents an upward-pointing spin button arrow in the pressed state.
